{{Annotation|250|160|What|font-weight=bold|font-size=25|color=black|background-color=#D8CAF3}}}}'''双流假说'''（{{lang-en|two-streams hypothesis}}）是一个颇具影响力的[[视觉|视觉]]信息神经处理模型。<ref>{{cite journal |author=Eyesenck MW, Keane MT. |title=Cognitive Psychology: A Student's Handbook |year=2010 |publisher= Psychology Press |location=Hove, UK}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=How do the two visual streams interact with each other?|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5380689/|last=Milner|first=A. D.|date=2017|journal=Experimental Brain Research|issue=5|doi=10.1007/s00221-017-4917-4|volume=235|pages=1297–1308|issn=0014-4819|pmc=5380689|pmid=28255843|access-date=2021-06-19|archive-date=2021-05-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210525180931/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5380689/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 这一假说认为人类[[大脑|大脑]]中拥有两种[[视觉系统|视觉系统]]，当视觉信息从[[枕叶|枕叶]]传出后经由两条路径传递，其中参与物体识别的腹流（{{lang|en|ventral stream}}）进入[[颞叶|颞叶]]，而参与空间位置信息处理的背流（{{lang|en|dorsal stream}}）则最终进入[[顶叶|顶叶]]。因而腹流又被称为内容通路（{{lang|en|what pathway}}），背流又被称为空间通路（{{lang|en|where pathway}}）。<ref name="Goodale1992">{{cite journal |author=Goodale MA, Milner AD |title=Separate visual pathways for perception and action |journal=Trends Neurosci. |volume=15 |issue=1 |pages=20–5 |year=1992 |pmid=1374953 |doi=10.1016/0166-2236(92)90344-8}}</ref>

